[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing session targeting the Apache Tika RTF parser triggered a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh‐severity security finding: `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution`. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash arose when the parser code deserialized data from an untrusted source via[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ObjectInputStream.readObject`, allowing unrestricted class or object creation [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbased on externally controlled input.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What happened  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During fuzz testing of the RTF parser harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`com.example.RTFParserFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe call chain reached Tika’s `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`, which uses [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ObjectInputStream` to read embedded objects from the RTF stream. Jazzer flagged [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis as a potential remote code execution vulnerability because arbitrary classes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan be instantiated during deserialization.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Unrestricted Java deserialization leading to Remote Code Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m through [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternally controlled data.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations and findings  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack trace shows the following sequence:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `jaz.Zer.readObject` → `java.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject`  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTF parser’s embedded‐object [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandler[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `TextExtractor.processGroupEnd` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `TextExtractor.extract`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `RTFParser.parseInline` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `RTFParser.parse`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – Entry point in the fuzzer at `RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne` and [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness invokes the parser but is not itself the root cause—it [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmerely exercises the vulnerable code path.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Define a new key in ParseContext, e.g., RTFParserConfig.ALLOW_JAVA_OBJECTS [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdefault false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Add a simple POJO or enum for RTFParserConfig with a boolean field [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowJavaObjects, defaulting to false.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Extend RTFEmbObjHandler to honor this flag:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In the constructor of RTFEmbObjHandler, read the flag from ParseContext:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      this.allowJavaObjects = [0m[1;35mparseContext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != null[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          && [0m[1;35mparseContext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.isAllowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Change the JAVA_OBJDATA branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m222[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If allowJavaObjects is false, skip deserialization entirely:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Option A [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: return immediately, or treat as generic binary data with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno extractObj invocation.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Option B [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpromote to objdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: call extractObj on the raw bytes without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserializing.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If allowJavaObjects is true, proceed with the existing [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObjectInputStream.readObject logic.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Provide an API for advanced users to enable safe deserialization:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Document in Tika’s parser configuration that embedded Java object [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization is disabled by default.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allow enabling it by supplying an RTFParserConfig instance to ParseContext [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore parsing:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     RTFParserConfig cfg = new [0m[1;35mRTFParserConfig[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mcfg.setAllowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ParseContext context = new [0m[1;35mParseContext[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mcontext.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class, cfg[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mparser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39minput, handler, metadata, context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Do not modify the fuzzing harness or any test code:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By disabling deserialization by default, the fuzzer will no longer reach [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, eliminating the RCE finding.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests that do not explicitly enable Java-object parsing will [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to behave unchanged.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Maintain backward compatibility:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Deprecate the new flag in the next major version for eventual removal if this [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeature is unused.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no other code paths are affected: all other branches [0m[1;39m([0m[39mEMBEDDING images,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOLE objects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unmodified.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExplanation:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach eliminates the unsafe call to `ObjectInputStream.readObject` when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing untrusted RTF streams, removing the RCE vector.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It preserves the overall embedded-object handling logic: when deserialization is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisabled, embedded object bytes are still available to downstream handlers as raw [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It uses the existing ParseContext mechanism to configure parser behavior, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfollowing Tika’s extensibility patterns, and avoids test or harness modifications.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effect: legitimate RTF files embedding Java-serialized objects [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill no longer be automatically extracted unless users explicitly enable the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeature. This is documented and can be re-enabled by trusted callers only.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzz test exposed a high-severity security issue in the RTF parser’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling of embedded Java object data: arbitrary byte streams are deserialized via [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, potentially allowing remote code execution. A [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was proposed to introduce a new `RTFParserConfig` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith an `allowJavaObjects`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, check that flag at runtime, and fall back to treating raw bytes as generic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata when deserialization is disabled. After applying the patch, the Microsoft RTF [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser module fails to compile, producing a cascade of syntax errors in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“illegal start of type” and “<identifier> expected”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent successful build.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarning rooted in `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, where raw bytes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom an embedded OLE object are passed unchecked into `new [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This unguarded deserialization allows an attacker to supply a malicious [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mserialized payload that can instantiate arbitrary classes on the classpath, leading[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto code execution.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace pinpoints the issue at lines around [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, in the parsing flow of Apache Tika’s RTF module.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added import for `org.apache.tika.parser.ParseContext`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a nested public class `RTFParserConfig` with a boolean [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowJavaObjects` flag, plus setter/getter methods.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m211[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, retrieved [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFParserConfig` from a `ParseContext` instance [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If no config is provided or `allowJavaObjects` is false, bypassed [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization and called `[0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, handler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead. [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOtherwise, performed the original object deserialization and downstream processing.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the deserialization in a try/catch handling both [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ClassNotFoundException` and `IOException`, recording exceptions via [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Compilation Errors After Patch  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maven compile reported [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, all “illegal [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of type” or “<identifier> expected,” plus “invalid method declaration; return[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtype required.”  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The errors cluster around the newly inserted lines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mroughly lines [0m[1;36m43[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m57[0m[39m and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magain near line [0m[1;36m251[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that the patch introduced misplaced tokens or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched braces.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reference to `context` in the patch is undefined in this scope, suggesting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe method signature or variable declarations for `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` were not updated to include a `ParseContext context` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The nested `public static class RTFParserConfig` appears before or outside the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menclosing class declaration, leading to top‐level class declaration conflicts.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File structure of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`: verify placement of imports, class [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations, and brace matching before and after the patch.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Method signatures and local variables in the code path handling [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`: ensure a `ParseContext context` is available and passed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough all relevant calls.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing use of `ParseContext` elsewhere in the RTF parser module to model the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect pattern for retrieving parser configuration.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build scripts or test harness code that invoke `RTFEmbObjHandler` to confirm [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow and where a `ParseContext` is constructed and passed.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consistency with Apache Tika coding conventions for introducing new [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration classes and context‐based feature flags.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer detected a high-severity security finding in the Apache Tika RTF parser:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munguarded Java deserialization in RTFEmbObjHandler’s `handleCompletedObject` method[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleads to potential remote code execution. To mitigate this, the patch attempt [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced a nested `RTFParserConfig` class and gated deserialization behind a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowJavaObjects`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The patch also updated imports, modified [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe handler’s constructor signature, and added metadata handling for raw bytes. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the Microsoft RTF parser module fails to compile with [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdozens of “class, interface, enum, or record expected” and “illegal start of type” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors, indicating misplaced code or mismatched braces in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer fuzzing run triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the RTF parser.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace points to `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject` entering the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`JAVA_OBJDATA` state and calling `new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No checks or configuration flags prevent deserialization of attacker-controlled [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte streams, exposing an RCE vector depending on the classpath.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash is reported by `Zer.reportFinding` deep in Java’s serialization code.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerable code path is specific to embedded Java objects in RTF files [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No memory limits or configuration flags are applied before deserializing.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removed unused imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`AtomicInteger`, `FilenameUtils`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and added [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ParseContext` and `UnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced four new instance fields: `handler`, `metadata`, `context`, and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memoryLimitInKb`, plus a `ByteArrayOutputStream os`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added a public static nested class `RTFParserConfig` with a boolean [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowJavaObjects` and corresponding getter/setter.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed the constructor signature to accept `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContentHandler handler, Metadata [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata, ParseContext context, int memoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In the `JAVA_OBJDATA` branch, retrieved `RTFParserConfig` from `context`. If [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization is disabled, treated the bytes as generic data; otherwise proceeded[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto deserialize.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrapped `[0m[1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` exceptions in `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead of throwing a `TikaException`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation fails in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` with ~[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m errors.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Errors include “class, interface, enum, or record expected” at import and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration lines, “illegal start of type,” and “invalid method declaration; return[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtype required.”  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log shows that code intended to be inside the class [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfields, constructor, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ended up outside class boundaries, indicating misplaced or unbalanced[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbraces.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The structure of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`: verify class opening/closing braces and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure the nested `RTFParserConfig` and new constructor are placed inside the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler` class.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Verify and restore the original class skeleton[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open RTFEmbObjHandler.java and remove any code that was inadvertently placed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore the `class RTFEmbObjHandler [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` line [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew fields, nested classes, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. All such additions from the last patch must be reverted to leave [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly imports, then the single `class RTFEmbObjHandler [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` declaration, followed by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe original fields:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add the ParseContext field inside the class[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after the existing fields block [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., after `private final int [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemoryLimitInKb;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private final ParseContext context;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Augment the existing constructor[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate the existing constructor[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       protected [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mContentHandler handler, Metadata metadata, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParseContext context, int memoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - At the end of its body, add:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.context = context;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the constructor still initializes:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.handler = handler;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.embeddedDocumentUtil = new [0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.os = [0m[1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayOutputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.memoryLimitInKb = memoryLimitInKb;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Import ParseContext[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the imports section at the top of the file, add:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       import org.apache.tika.parser.ParseContext;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any duplicate or misplaced ParseContext imports.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Introduce the RTFParserConfig nested class[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Just before the final closing brace of RTFEmbObjHandler, insert:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m** Controls whether embedded Java objects are deserialized *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public static class RTFParserConfig [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           public void [0m[1;35msetAllowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           public boolean [0m[1;35misAllowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Gate the JAVA_OBJDATA branch[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside the existing handleCompletedObject [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor equivalent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method, find:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstate == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m original unguarded deserialization[0m[33m...[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace its contents with:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m fetch parser config from context[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       RTFParserConfig cfg = [0m[1;35mcontext.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcfg == null || ![0m[1;35mcfg.isAllowJavaObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m deserialization disabled: treat bytes as raw[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[32m"application/octet-stream"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, handler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               Object obj = new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            [0m[1;35mMediaType.text[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"plain"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          handler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mClassNotFoundException | IOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1;39m([0m[39me, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Clean up imports[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure only one import of UnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream exists [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCommons IO or Tika one as appropriate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove unused imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAtomicInteger, FilenameUtils if still unused[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. Verify RTFParser call site[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In RTFParser.java, confirm the constructor invocation:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       new [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandler, metadata, context, [0m[1;35mgetMemoryLimitInKb[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     still matches the revised constructor signature.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m. Re-run `mvn compile` to verify that all “class, interface, enum, or record [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected” and “illegal start of type” errors have disappeared.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By moving all new fields, constructor logic, and the nested config class inside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe single class body, we restore brace balance and eliminate stray top-level [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations that caused compilation errors.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adding only one new field [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ParseContext context`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and augmenting the existing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor preserves the original EmbeddedDocumentUtil–based parsing pipeline.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The nested `RTFParserConfig` pattern follows existing Tika parsers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFParserConfig[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and gating the deserialization in the JAVA_OBJDATA branch [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meffectively mitigates the RCE vector while retaining legacy functionality when [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menabled.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Exporting the same four-argument constructor ensures existing callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe fuzz [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness and RTFParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continue to compile without changes.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach does not modify any harness code or external dependencies, and does[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot remove functionality, but instead tightens the security check around Java [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization. Potential side effects are minimal—embedded Java objects will be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignored by default; users who need them can explicitly enable via [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ParseContext#[0m[1;35mset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserConfig.class, config[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue reports a high-severity Jazzer fuzzer finding: an unguarded Java  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization path in the RTF parser [1m([0m`RTFEmbObjHandler`[1m)[0m that can lead to remote [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code execution. In response, a patch was attempted that introduces a parser         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         configuration flag [1m([0m`RTFParserConfig.allowJavaObjects`[1m)[0m to disable Java object      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization by default. The patch modifies the handler to fetch this flag from  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         a `ParseContext`, conditionally skips deserialization when disabled, and adds a     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         nested `RTFParserConfig` class. After applying the patch, the module fails to       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         compile with a cascade of “illegal start of type” and “class, interface, enum, or   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         record expected” errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, suggesting mis-placed or        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         mismatched braces and improper placement of the new nested class.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzing run triggers `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in the RTF parser.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace pinpoints `RTFEmbObjHandler.readObject` where `new                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is called unconditionally on untrusted input.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Metadata extraction and `extractObj` then treat the deserialized object’s      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mtoString[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` bytes as text, enabling execution of arbitrary classes on the          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classpath.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations from the Issue                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The code immediately deserializes embedded Java objects                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`[1m)[0m without any configuration guard.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerability arises from unrestricted `[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`, a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classic deserialization risk.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Imports:                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Added `import org.apache.tika.parser.ParseContext;`                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Fields:                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Introduced `private final ParseContext context;` alongside existing fields.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Constructor:                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Updated to accept a `ParseContext context` parameter and assign it to the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         new field.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Passed `context` into `new [1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil[0m[1m([0mcontext[1m)[0m`.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Deserialization Branch [1m([0m`EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`[1m)[0m:                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Retrieved `RTFParserConfig cfg = [1;35mcontext.get[0m[1m([0mRTFParserConfig.class[1m)[0m;`        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + If `cfg` is null or `![1;35mcfg.isAllowJavaObjects[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`, skip deserialization, set   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `EMB_CLASS` to `[32m"application/octet-stream"[0m`, and call `[1;35mextractObj[0m[1m([0mbytes, …[1m)[0m`.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Else, wrap the original `ObjectInputStream` logic in a try-catch; on         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exception call `[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1m([0me, metadata[1m)[0m`.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Configuration Class:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + Appended a public static nested class `RTFParserConfig` with a boolean flag  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `allowJavaObjects` and getters/setters.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Compilation Result                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Maven reports [1;36m24[0m errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, all variants of:           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + “illegal start of type”                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              + “[1m<[0m[1;95midentifier[0m[39m> expected”  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + “invalid method declaration; return type required”  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + “class, interface, enum, or record expected”  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors occur around the inserted code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline ~[0m[1;36m237[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and at the end of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile, indicating misplaced braces or that the new nested class was added inside a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod body rather than at the class level.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify the placement of opening/closing braces in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure the new nested `RTFParserConfig` class resides inside the top-level [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler` class and not inside another method.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine the method where `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` is handled to confirm that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `else if` block is properly closed before the insertion of the nested class.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review constructor signatures and calls in related classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., where [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler` is instantiated[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure the added `ParseContext context` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter is propagated correctly.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check imports and package declarations for consistency and ensure no missing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemicolons or stray tokens around the patched regions.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect surrounding code in `TextExtractor` and `RTFParser` to verify that a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ParseContext` is available and that users of `RTFParserConfig` can actually [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigure and pass it in.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis information should allow developers to reapply the patch, locate and fix the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbrace/placement issues, and validate that the guard against untrusted [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization is properly integrated.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
